The paper deals with the problem of computing functional aggregate queries in a distributed network, which is a topic that falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a new notion of 'width' for Generalized Hypertree Decompositions, which is a topic that falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper uses communication complexity techniques to prove topology dependent bounds, which is a topic that falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT).
